The paper proposes a method for one-class classification using deep learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of deep learning suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on image datasets such as CIFAR and ImageNet suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of adversarial perturbations, which is a common technique in adversarial machine learning, suggesting it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for one-class classification, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
